Europe
------
[1] The Netherlands (Zeeland)
Date: Mon 28 Oct 2013
Source: Dutch News [edited]
http://www.dutchnews.nl/news/archives/2013/10/measles_kills_teenage_girl_in.php


A 17-year-old girl from Zeeland has died from complications after contracting measles, the Netherlands Public Health Institute [RIVM] said on Monday [28 Oct 2013]. The girl, who died on Sat 26 Oct 2013, had not been vaccinated against measles. The Dutch Bible belt has been hit by a measles epidemic in recent months, and over 2000 people have been officially diagnosed with the disease. The real total is likely to be far higher because many people do not report the illness to their doctors, the RIVM said.

Three people died during the last outbreak, which ran from 1996 to 2000.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[In a press statement on the Ministry of Health Welfare and Sport website, there is a press release on this case and outbreak: "Since May, cases of measles are being reported in The Netherlands, especially among the unvaccinated population. The last measles outbreak was in 1999/2000. More than 3000 patients have been reported in that period, 3 patients died.

"Up to now, a number of 2016 patients with measles were reported. The actual number of patients is probably much higher because many patients do not visit the doctor. 121 Patients have been hospitalized, including 61 patients with pneumonia and 1 patient with a brain inflammation (encephalitis)." http://www.rivm.nl/en/Documents_and_publications/Common_and_Present/Newsmessages/2013/Teenage_girl_dies_after_measles_infection.

As in previous outbreaks, there has been significant morbidity and now mortality associated with a vaccine preventable disease in a predominantly unvaccinated population group. - Mod.MPP]

A HealthMap ProMED-mail map can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/1r1l.]

