[2] Russia (Chelyabinsk)
Date: Fri 25 Oct 2013
Source: Interfax Rossiya [in Russian, trans. Mod.CP, edited]
http://www.interfax-russia.ru/Ural/news.asp?id=445472&sec=1671


In the Chelyabinsk region, for the 1st time in 7 years, 38 cases of measles have been registered, an unacceptable situation according to the Chief Public Health physician in the Chelyabinsk Oblast [region]. Measles cases were reported during September and October 2013 in the Troitskii and Kokinskoi regions and in Chelyabinsk.

36 of the 38 cases occurred in the Roma community; one was the child of an immigrant from Kyrgyzstan, and one child in Chelyabinsk contracted the disease from care providers. These cases comprised 4 adults and 34 children. Of these cases, 28 had not been vaccinated against measles; another 8 had received only one vaccination, and 2 had received the required 2 vaccinations.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail from HealthMap Alerts
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The Chelyabinsk Oblast is a federal district of Russia in the Ural Mountains region on the border of Europe and Asia. Its administrative center is the city of Chelyabinsk. Population: 3 476 217 (2010 Census). The location of the Chelyabinsk Oblast can be viewed on the maps at: http://russiatrek.org/chelyabinsk-oblast. As elsewhere in Russia, recent outbreaks of measles are being attributed to Roma migrants and other immigrant populations. - Mod.CP

A HealthMap ProMED-mail map can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/60ZE.]

